The LLM synthesizes coherent and contextually relevant responses by processing the top-K re-ranked retrieval results from previous stages. This input concentration mechanism ensures the model receives the most pertinent information for each query. Through carefully designed prompt engineering, the retrieved content is transformed into structured input parameters that enhance the LLM’s contextual comprehension. The model then leverages its language generation capabilities to produce informative, query-specific responses. This generation process is formally expressed as16\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
